### Aim

The idea is to find all the places that are warm and sunny within a radius of a location. 

Assume that a place is "warm and sunny" if within the last 24 hours, the max temperature was above 20C and the average temperature was above 15C.

### Prerequisites

Node-RED `package.json` needs to include the following packages:

- [overpass-frontend](https://www.npmjs.com/package/overpass-frontend) - [doco](https://rawgit.com/plepe/overpass-frontend/master/doc/OverpassFrontend.html)
- [geolib](https://www.npmjs.com/package/geolib) - [doco](https://github.com/manuelbieh/geolib#functions)

### Inputs

The `msg` object is a assumed to have two attributes:

```javascript
msg.myposition = {
    latitude: 52.52437,
    longitude: 13.41053
};
msg.radius_meters = 1000000; // 1000km in meters
```

### Flow Explanation

The flow begins by <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="6339393a9d8f3191">obtaining all weather stations</a> and immediately the data is <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="1db155010ca59ca9">split</a> so that each line of the data is handled simultaneously. The <a class="ahl-group-only" data-ids="d2a05e6c6a12df63">`get weather station details`</a> group extracts the location of the station and ensures that a station is within range of the initial position. For all those stations that are, the <a class="ahl-group-only" data-ids="c6efee6e78378266">`for each station within radius request weather details`</a> group obtains the weather data. All requests are made simultaneously.

The <a class="" data-ids="">join node</a> collects together all the results of handling each line of the <a class="" data-ids="">original list of stations</a> has been handled. Each line can either:

- <a class="ahl-link-node" data-ids="444775194ca43392,97ad80fa5d0d32e9">not be parse, i.e. is a comment or does not contain a station location</a>
- <a class="ahl-link-node" data-ids="444775194ca43392,97ad80fa5d0d32e9">define a station that is located too far away</a>
- <a class="ahl-link-node" data-ids="4c38479e195a9f6a,97ad80fa5d0d32e9">the request for the station data failed</a>


